tip.text: Very homely red chicken curry, yum. nice place to idle.
Great coffees. Previous try of their brunch item the Double Barrel was underwhelming though- toast was too hard and the toppings just sloppily done. Just get the coffee! Wifi pw: cupoflove
Opened by an Italian guy from the Naples who has been in Lombok for 10 years, joined by his son for 2 years. Ask for special pastas if they are around. Otherwise the seafood platter is incredible.
The beef pho was fantastic. Coupled with an authentic Thai ice tea, perfect. Wifi login: bobun password: getfat
Best Italian restaurant in Seminyak. Everything is authentic and so delicious, with a romantic and cosy ambiance! Try the white wine made from Balinese grapes too.
Real crowded even on weekdays. Fancy drinks. The red duck curry is really spicy but pretty good. Sitting arrangement is not ideal with low tables for meals for those who cannot get a table.
